            All Events
            <br><br><br>
            %p
              WARNING:  Choosing to "delete" an event should rarely be done.  The guest list for that event will be deleted along with the event.  The guest list contains the names and emails of event attendees.  You likely would want to send an event cancellation email out before cancelling an event.  However, if you delete an event below, the guest list (with guest emails) is deleted too, and you will have *no way* of contacting all the people who registered to attend the event.  The guest list (and emails of attendees) should be looked at before an event is deleted.






        %table#events.table
          %thead
            "People Attending" - No. of people registered to attend the event *through the website*
            <br>
            "Capacity" - Maximum no. of people allowed to register through site
            %tr
              -# Note there are invisible spaces after each of following th titles
              %th Event Name           
              %th Description          
              %th Host          
              %th Start Time                    
              %th End Time                      
              %th Venue                
              %th Address                                 
              %th People Attending
              %th Capacity
          %tbody
            - @events.each do |event|
              %tr
                %td= event.event_name 
                %td= event.description
                %td= event.host
                %td= event.start_date_time.to_formatted_s(:long_ordinal)
                %td= event.end_date_time.to_formatted_s(:long_ordinal)
                %td= event.venue
                %td= event.address

                %td= link_to "Delete Event", event, method: :destroy

                %td= event.num_persons_attending
                %td= event.max_capacity
                %td= button_to 'Delete event and *guest list*', event_path(event), :method => :delete, :confirm => 'EXTREMELY IMPORTANT- remember to check if there are site users who already signed up for this event.  If anyone signed up to attend this event, and you delete the event now, these persons will not be notified that the event they signed up for has been deleted.  You should get the emails for these people first, before you delete this event (so you can send out an email to them, canceling the event).  ***AFTER AN EVENT HAS BEEN DELETED, THERE IS NO WAY TO ACCESS THE EMAILS AND NAMES OF THE PEOPLE WHO REGISTERED TO ATTEND THAT EVENT.***                                                                                                                      Click CANCEL to do nothing.  Click OK to go ahead and delete guest list and event.'

